pr_title: Added Google Benchmark to the project.
pr_body:
This PR adds Google Benchmark, as a first step to having some benchmarking on the math functions defined in this repository so that we can quantitatively measure the performance of the functions and classes defined in here.

I did my best to mimic the existing project structure, and took inspiration from [VecMem](https://github.com/acts-project/vecmem/) where appropriate.

Nevertheless, I have changed it to be more in line with the `algebra-plugins` way of doing things.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 19, 6, 25, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wermos', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 901054840, 'comment_body': 'Here, I actually copied the beginning portion (that is, the copyright stuff) from the [`extern/googletest/CMakeLists.txt`](https://github.com/acts-project/algebra-plugins/blob/d94ef468209a0c6eadb67130bf50ca37a19a40e7/extern/googletest/CMakeLists.txt#L3). Should I change it in this PR, or make a new PR for it? It looks to me like there are quite a few places which have the copyright line still on 2021:

', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 19, 6, 30, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wermos', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 901055142, 'comment_body': 'I plan on adding some benchmarks in the next PR itself. Plus, the default option (for now, at least), is `FALSE`. However, if you think it will cause problems (maybe in the CI or something), then I can remove it and add it into the next PR.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 19, 6, 33, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wermos', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 901078529, 'comment_body': 'You can change it in this PR. In general, when you add a new file, the copyright should be set to the year it is deployed. If you modify old code in existing files, the copyright will be extended to the year it was modified e.g. ```2021-2022```. It is not tragic if you forget it, as long as a copyright is present', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 19, 9, 51, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'niermann999', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 901169869, 'comment_body': 'You can leave it if you like', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 19, 23, 14, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'beomki-yeo', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: ci: Cleaned up the workflow files a little.
pr_body: There were many instances of trailing `--` in the CMake commands, followed by nothing, which I removed. Moreover, many of the targets were passed  to the underlying build system as a build-system-specific flag. I changed those to make it so that the `--target` CMake flag is used.

Can you revert this bit?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 5, 13, 3, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'paulgessinger', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 939468238, 'comment_body': "I'll do so, and add a comment about why this is necessary too.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 6, 2, 16, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wermos', 'type': 'User'}]
